Key Match Events: Tyrese Haliburton tallied 25 points, 10 assists, three steals and two rebounds.
Pascal Siakam added 25 points and nine rebounds.
Buddy Hield helped lead the Warriors with 17 points on 6-of-19 shooting from the field with three made 3-pointers.
Pat Spencer notched a new career-high with 18 points on 7-of-12 shooting from the floor in 20 minutes.
Rookie Quinten Post scored six points in seven minutes off the bench and buried his first career 3-pointer.
Pre-Game Insights: The Warriors were without multiple key veteran players, including Steph Curry, Andrew Wiggins, and Draymond Green.
